Category:
Market Research & Analysis (Marketing & Communications)
Government - Local (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Overview
  
This role will strategically map LGAQ’s engagement with members to identify and utilise opportunities to enhance engagement and build loyalty.  Working collaboratively across the Association, this position plays a critical role in planning, coordinating and creating insights about member engagement activities to help maximise value for members.

The role leads a small team and reports directly to the Head of Assist. The Assist workstream is also responsible for delivering a range of support and services for members including, governance and workforce support and advice, communications to members and management of the LGAQ’s events program. 

This is a full time role based in Newstead, Queensland. The role will work across Workstreams and with elected members, council staff and other external stakeholders to deliver results.

The right candidate for this role will fit in with our collaborative culture and have a strong commitment to supporting our members.  Flexible work arrangements will be negotiated with the successful candidate, however the role will be required to be office based at least three days per week. Work outside of ordinary office hours will be required at times. 

Applications from people with diverse lived experience and identities are strongly encouraged, as the more diverse our team is, the better we are able to represent our diverse membership.

Key Responsibilities
  
This role will have a number of responsibilities including:

Member Intelligence

In consultation with internal stakeholders, develop an evidence-based annual member engagement plan and continue to monitor and report on its implementation and progress
Work with internal teams and individuals to develop a segmented approach to member engagement activities and events, including a reporting framework to improve understanding of key needs of different membership groups
Work with segment teams to ensure segment plans are developed and implemented and utilize corporate systems to monitor their effectiveness
Maintain key membership contact details (VIPs), whole of organisation engagement data and insights to be able to provide on-demand reporting to the LGAQ President, Board, CEO, ELT and colleagues on emerging issues and member sentiment
Proactively advise the Executive Leadership Team on member engagement insights and recommend measures to enhance member value and loyalty
Facilitate regular meetings of customer engagement and marketing staff from across the LGAQ Group (including Peak Services/Local Buy, Digital & LGMS Insurance Schemes) for the purposes of coordinating marketing efforts and sharing customer intelligence
Establish practical tools and approaches to capture and track member engagement and loyalty to inform meaningful decision making
Ensure the integrity, validity and governance of member and engagement data is upheld
Member Value

Support the communication of the role, function, and value of the LGAQ to members, including Mayors, Councillors, CEOs and Senior Officers through a variety of approaches and tailored member engagement experiences
Contribute to the development of key communications regarding LGAQ progress and member value, including, but not limited to, Congruent, annual report, annual invoicing, events, and other council presentations and briefings
Develop member onboarding approaches targeted at improving member comprehension of the role, activities, and value of the LGAQ for both those working in and leading Queensland local governments, as well as new LGAQ employees
Culture Contributor

Contribute to the LGAQ culture through application of the CARE Behaviours and participation in workplace activities
Personally adhere and to all workplace relevant legislation and LGAQ policies.
About You
  
To be successful in this role you will have:

Experience developing and delivering evidence-based programs and strategic initiatives that build member/customer loyalty within a diverse membership group
Knowledge of the local government environment and issues and challenges faced by councils across Queensland will be highly regarded
Relevant tertiary qualifications in Business, Marketing, Communications or similar fields
Proven ability to work collaboratively, build constructive relationships and influence outcomes with a range of stakeholders
Demonstrated ability to lead a small high performing team to deliver outcomes
Proven ability to develop and coach team members
High level written, verbal and presentation skills to effectively communicate with diverse stakeholders
Proven project management skills and experience running a number of concurrent initiatives to meet deadlines and outcomes
Well developed problem analysis and solving skills
Proven ability to analyse and interpret data to inform decision making
A current open driver’s licence and ability to travel.
About LGAQ
  
The LGAQ is the peak industry body and registered industrial employer organisation for Queensland’s 77 local councils, a sector that employs in excess of 44,000 Queenslanders across circa 250 various professions. We advocate for our members’ interests at a state and federal level and support their drive to innovate and improve service delivery. 
  
We have an inclusive and caring culture underpinned by our CARE Behaviours@LGAQ. LGAQ people demonstrate Caring Accountable Respectful and Engaged behaviours. As an equal opportunity employer, LGAQ encourages applications from candidates with diverse backgrounds. We are also a pet friendly workplace.
  
We embrace flexible working arrangements in a hybrid model with options for time in the office, working from home and in some cases, travel to our member councils.
  
LGAQ may undertake a range of pre-employment screening including Police Check and psychometric assessment as part of the selection process.

Your Application
  
Use the link to send us your CV and an optional one page cover letter highlighting your fit for this role. We will commence discussions with suitable candidates as applications are received.
 
If you have any further questions after reading the requirements above, please call our People and Culture team on 3000 2227.

About us

Indigitise is a locally grown ICT consulting and delivery partner, supporting Federal Government clients to deliver secure, scalable, and people-centred digital and ERP solutions. We specialise in complex transformation programs across large Commonwealth environments.

The opportunity

We are seeking an experienced Integration Analyst to support a large, complex ERP transformation program within a federal government environment.

This role focuses on end-to-end integration across the procure-to-pay value chain, supporting a SAP S/4HANA ERP platform. You will work across procurement, logistics, supply chain, and engineering streams to ensure business processes, integrations, and documentation are aligned with policy and operational needs.

Must be an AUSTRALIAN CITIZEN with BASELINE CLEARANCE

What you’ll do

Support cross-stream process and system integration across large, end-to-end ICT and ERP programs.

Conduct investigative and analytical work to determine business requirements for ongoing ERP uplift and enhancement.

Specify, map, and help implement effective business processes through improvements in systems, practices, and organisational change.

Work closely with stakeholders to ensure procurement and purchasing workflows in S/4HANA align with commercial and policy requirements.

Support ERP adoption by identifying process, policy, and training uplift opportunities.

Liaise with business and technical stakeholders to support procurement and commercial outcomes.

Review and support development of technical and integration documentation to ensure consistency across value chains.

Operate within a Linux environment, including exposure to basic shell scripting and crontab.

What you’ll bring (Essential)

Prior transactional experience with SAP S/4HANA, with confidence navigating ERP systems.

Demonstrated experience in procurement or logistics, ideally within large or regulated environments.

Familiarity with integration points across procurement, supply chain, and engineering functions.

Experience supporting large-scale, end-to-end ICT or ERP programs.

Strong stakeholder engagement skills and the ability to work effectively across business and technical teams.

Ability to work independently with sound judgement in a complex delivery environment.

Nice to have (Desirable)

Exposure to commercial and procurement modules in S/4HANA.

Experience supporting ERP adoption, change, or training uplift activities.

Strong written and verbal communication skills.

Experience working within the Commonwealth or highly regulated environments.

How to apply

If you’re an Integration Analyst with strong SAP S/4HANA and procurement integration experience, and you’re interested in contributing to a major ERP transformation program, we’d love to hear from you.

Please reach out to us at operations@indigitise.com.au
or call Manoj on 0468 492 531 for a confidential discussion.

Job Title: Manager - Strategic Planning and Stress Testing
Ad Text:
About the Role

We are seeking an experienced Manager - Strategic Planning & Stress Testing to join our Sydney based global banking & Finance organisation. This highly visible role is responsible for delivering enterprise‑wide stress testing, climate scenario analysis, and forward‑looking strategic insights that directly support Board‑level reporting and regulatory obligations.
As a key strategic partner, you will work closely with the CFO, CRO, Risk & Compliance, Strategy & Planning, and regional stakeholders, influencing decision‑making and contributing to the organisation's financial resilience and long‑term planning.

Key Responsibilities

Perform the annual APRA stress testing process, including developing economic scenarios and preparing Board‑ready insights.
Deliver climate stress testing and support climate‑related financial disclosures aligned with evolving government requirements.
Coordinate, review, and challenge the Annual Operating Plan (AOP), providing analysis, insights, and strategic recommendations.
Review and challenge risk models across Retail and Wholesale portfolios.
Provide analytical support for forecasting, ICCAP, sensitivity testing, and risk appetite setting.
Prepare high‑quality presentations and reports for Regulators, Board Committees, RMM, CFO and CRO.
Maintain governance standards related to stress testing and proactively identify emerging risks and gaps.
Build strong relationships across Finance, Risk & Compliance, and global/regional teams.


Skills & Experience
5+ years' experience in a similar Banking & Financial Services role.
Strong understanding of banking products, transfer pricing and balance sheet dynamics.
Proven experience in enterprise‑wide and portfolio stress testing.
Knowledge of credit risk modelling, regulatory frameworks, capital adequacy and liquidity management.
Familiarity with APRA RWA methodologies (Standardised & AIRB).
Coding skills (Python, R, SAS) desirable; TM1/HMI experience essential.
Excellent written communication, analytical strength and advanced Microsoft Office skills.
Ability to work under pressure and manage competing priorities with accuracy.
Strong stakeholder engagement and ability to influence senior executives.
Experience within Financial Planning & Analysis would be considered

Job Title: Senior Treasury & Corporate Finance Analyst (Max Term)
Ad Text:
Company description:



Pacific Blue is a leading owner, operator, and developer of renewable energy assets. We operate a high quality and diversified portfolio of wind, hydro, and solar assets, as well as offering a range of competitive energy products, delivering value to our retail energy customer base. With the growing importance of renewable energy in Australia's future, a career with us is more than just a job. You will be helping us to lead Australia to an affordable clean energy future that deliver positive social, environmental, and economic outcomes.



Job description:



The Role

This maximum-term role is a critical part of Pacific Blue's Treasury and Corporate Finance function, delivering high-quality financial analysis, modelling, and insights to support investment decisions, funding strategies, and long-term financial planning. The position contributes directly to the organisation's financial performance, capital structure, and growth objectives.

Working closely with senior stakeholders, the role supports informed decision-making across renewable energy investments, capital planning, and treasury operations, aligned with Pacific Blue's broader business and financial strategies.

This is a 12-month maximum-term, full-time position based in Melbourne.

What you'll be responsible for:

Corporate Finance

Develop and maintain financial models and scenario analysis to support the evaluation of renewable energy projects, strategic initiatives, and investment decisions.
Conduct industry and market research to inform business cases, with a focus on the energy transition, decarbonisation, and evolving regulatory environments.
Support capital budgeting and long-term financial planning for generation assets and infrastructure investments.
Assist in the preparation of financial papers, presentations, and analysis for the Executive team and Board, including project updates and strategic proposals.

Treasury

Contribute to capital planning and liquidity management across a portfolio of renewable energy assets.
Monitor debt facilities, covenant compliance, and project-level financing arrangements, including green and sustainability-linked loans.
Support treasury reporting and maintain effective relationships with banking and financing partners.
Assist with analysis related to interest rates, foreign exchange exposures, and funding strategies for renewable projects.


Profile description:



To be successful in this role you will have:

Knowledge and experience:

Bachelor's degree in finance, Accounting, Economics, or related field
CPA/CA/CFA qualification (or working towards) is desirable
Min 3 years of experience in corporate finance, investment banking, transaction services, or within the energy/infrastructure sectors
Prior experience in Corporate Finance or treasury within the energy, infrastructure, or utilities sector is desirable
Exposure to renewable energy project finance, PPA structures, or grid-scale energy investments is desirable
Strong understanding of financial statements, capital structures, and investment metrics relevant to infrastructure or energy generation
Experience working with senior stakeholders and managing multiple priorities

Skills:

Advanced Excel skills with proven experience in financial modelling and valuation techniques
Strong attention to detail, analytical thinking, and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and presentation skills


We offer:



What We offer
At Pacific Blue, as a leading renewable energy provider for the past 30 years, we know what it takes to create real change. Our success isn't solely driven by our technology, investments, or assets—it's powered by our people. Our passionate and dedicated team is the reason we can make 100% clean energy available today, not tomorrow.

We provide a wide range of benefits including:

Discounts to Home Energy and Health Insurance
Purchased leave program
Free Employee Assistance Program
Generous parental leave options
Work and life balance and flexible work arrangements
Modern open plan office with ergonomic standing desks
Office location next to Southern Cross Station and tram stops
A team that is inclusive and supportive

Pacific Blue is committed to fostering an inclusive and diverse work environment where individuals in each of our business units feel involved, supported, respected, and treated fairly. We believe that embracing people with diverse capabilities, perspectives, and experiences will enrich our team and provide competitive advantages to our business. This has resulted in our recognition by the DCA as an Inclusive Employer.

If you require accommodations or adjustments, we encourage you to inform us so that we can support you throughout the application process.

Only candidates with the eligible right to work in Australia will be considered.

If you share our vision of creating a sustainable future and believe in making a positive impact, please click the 'apply' button to express your interest.

Recruiters are kindly asked not to apply.

About us 
We are an award winning, national $16B public offer industry fund focused on the education and community sectors. Working for NGS Super means being part of something bigger and working to make a difference to our members and their financial future.  

Our people are key to our success, and as we expand, we’re committed to finding and retaining the right talent to take on the journey.  As well as a flexible and fun workplace, we offer competitive benefits including additional leave entitlements, personal & professional development and health & wellbeing programs. 

Click on the video below to learn more! 

The Role 
The Senior Investment Operations Analyst plays a key role in ensuring the Fund’s investment and financial activities run smoothly and accurately. In this role, you’ll take ownership of delivering timely, precise financial and investment reporting, while ensuring everything aligns with internal policies and regulatory requirements. 

You’ll build strong relationships with both internal and external stakeholders, streamline and strengthen investment operations processes, and contribute directly to the Fund’s financial accounts and audit processes. 

What you’ll do

Manage relationships between the Trustee, Custodians, Investment Managers, external Auditors and Financial Accountants.
Assist monitor compliance with contractual obligations, including management of incidents raised internally or by our service providers.
Ensure the accurate and timely preparation and presentation of investment operational reports and statistics.
Ensure the accurate and timely supply of reporting by our providers, including KPI reporting and compliance attestations.
Support the implementation of the decisions of the board and committee e.g. Changes to asset allocation, funding or termination of managers, adjusting and setting fee accruals, completion of proxy voting documentation.
Work with the risk and compliance manager to ensure adherence to and reporting against relevant risk control procedures as per the risk management framework. 
Manage the daily unit pricing process including cash-flows.
Oversee the completion of instructions to the custodian, as well as the calculation and monitoring of investment accruals.
Manage the ORR and ensure compliance with SPS 114 and AASB standards as it relates to both the broader fund and investments and review the policy annually.
Implement policy, process, internal controls, financial delegations, company registers and records.

About you 
With previous experience in a similar role and an analytical mindset, you will bring the following key skills:

Qualifications in a relevant discipline (e.g. B.acc, b.com, b econ etc.) or a proven track record of achievement in the area.
Ability to maintain a current knowledge of the superannuation industry, general superannuation law and key features of the fund.
Demonstrated commitment to achieving the needs of members and employers.
Ability to interpret financial and economic data.
Knowledge and experience of fund accounting principles, management of risk and compliance in the superannuation industry.
Demonstrated operational experience across both Public and Private Market Investments and Fund of Fund Structures.
Experience in outsourced provider relationships to ensure the delivery of agreed service standards.
Excellent attention to detail and communication skills.
Experience in superannuation fund management is nice to have but not essential.

If you have a proven track record of success in Investment Operations and want to work for a truly member-focused super fund, we would love to hear from you.

We are a super fund that has an exceptional work culture, provides a diverse offering in developing our people and you can be a part of it while earning an attractive remuneration package! 

Interested and suitably qualified candidates should submit a copy of their updated CV. 

Please note that to be eligible for this role, you are required to have permanent Australian working rights and residency. 

We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a workplace that values diversity, equity, and respect for all individuals.

About the role


Our client is seeking an experienced Data & Information Architect to lead the design, evolution, and governance of enterprise-wide data and information architecture.

Reporting to the Enterprise Architect, this role plays a pivotal part in shaping the organisation's technology roadmap and supporting its transformation into a truly insight-driven organisation. You will work in close partnership with ICT leadership, business stakeholders, and external vendors to design secure, scalable, and future-ready data solutions that enable informed decision-making and deliver meaningful outcomes for South Australians.

Key responsibilities


As the Data & Information Architect, you will:

Lead the design and development of enterprise data and information architecture across multiple viewpoints and levels of abstraction
Assess current and target state architectures, defining transition roadmaps to address capability gaps
Act as a trusted architectural adviser to senior leaders, providing strategic guidance and thought leadership
Develop and present architecture landscapes, roadmaps, UML, ER diagrams, and data models
Design and implement robust data governance frameworks, including data quality, lineage, taxonomies, and security controls
Lead and guide the adoption of data platforms, including data warehousing, analytics, and emerging technologies
Define and promote best practices for data integration, modelling, and information management
Collaborate with analytics, application, infrastructure, and operations teams to deliver cohesive, integrated solutions
Represent the organisation on cross-agency forums and provide specialist architectural consultancy
Mentor and guide teams in data management standards, practices, and continuous improvement
What you'll bring
Proven experience leading enterprise data and information architecture in complex environments
Strong capability in defining current and future state architectures and developing transition plans
Hands-on experience with data warehousing, analytics, big data, and data integration technologies
Sound knowledge of government ICT, information architecture, and security standards
Experience contributing to business cases and enterprise-wide transformation initiatives
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to articulate complex technical concepts clearly
A collaborative and strategic mindset, with the ability to work independently under broad direction
A strong commitment to fostering a safe, inclusive, and ethical workplace
Desirable qualifications
Tertiary qualification in Information Technology, Computer Science, Business, or a related discipline
TOGAF or other recognised architecture certifications
Membership of relevant professional bodies

We are also open to looking at mid-senior level data specialists / practitioners who have designed data platforms end-to-end, can articulate architecture, and can influence decisions. If you have been involved in solution design and deployments working in the capacity of a Lead Data Engineer, Data Platform Lead, Data Solution Designer, Technical Lead (Data); Your experience would touch upon :

Designing a data platform / lake / warehouse from scratch
Making decisions about how data flows between systems
Chosing tools and patterns (ETL, ELT, streaming, APIs)
Defining data models, integration patterns, and standards
Working with enterprise architects or solution architects
Written architecture artefacts (even informally):
Logical / conceptual data models
Current vs future state diagrams
Data flow diagrams
Integration maps

A leading financial services organisation is seeking a Principal Data Engineer to shape the future of its enterprise data platforms. This is a strategic, high‑impact individual contributor role where you will set technical direction, define engineering standards, and solve the organisation’s most complex data challenges.

You will work across cloud-native data platforms, influence senior engineers and architects, and drive the shift toward real‑time, event-driven and AI‑enabled data capabilities.

What You’ll Do

Act as the senior technical authority for data engineering across multiple domains.

Define and lead the technical vision for modern, scalable, cloud-based data platforms.

Drive architectural decisions and build hands‑on prototypes to validate new approaches.

Modernise traditional batch/ETL practices into near real-time, event-driven data patterns.

Harmonise operational and analytical workloads using the right combination of cloud-native tools.

Work with senior engineers, product leaders, and architects to uplift engineering practices.

Solve the organisation’s hardest data problems: performance, scale, latency, modelling, lineage, governance.

Enable AI-driven capabilities by ensuring data quality, freshness, observability, and platform readiness.

Influence without authority — no direct reports — leading through credibility and technical depth.

What You Bring
Deep Data Engineering Expertise (Essential)

Extensive experience designing and operating large-scale data platforms (data lakes, warehouses, integration hubs).

Strong traditional data engineering skills:
SQL, Python, ETL/ELT, data modelling, warehousing, pipeline optimisation.

Experience working with complex, multi-source environments at enterprise scale.

Cloud & Modern Architecture (Essential)

Hands-on experience with GCP or similar cloud platforms.

Strong understanding of key cloud data services such as:
BigQuery, Spanner, Bigtable, Dataflow/Beam, Dataproc, object storage, orchestration tools.

Ability to choose the right technology for transactional vs analytical workloads.

Event-Driven / Real-Time Engineering (Strategic Advantage)

Experience designing or delivering event-driven architectures & streaming pipelines.

Understanding of pub/sub, CDC/outbox patterns, idempotency, ordering, late data handling.

Leadership Through Influence

Proven ability to influence senior engineers, architects, and product stakeholders.

Experience navigating complex environments with healthy challenge and clear decision-making.

Strong communication skills able to articulate complex engineering strategies simply.

AI Awareness

Understanding of how modern data platforms enable AI/ML.

Experience using AI to improve engineering workflows or data capabilities is highly valued.

A well-known Australian organisation is expanding its analytics capability and is looking for a Senior Insights Analyst who is exceptional with SAS and equally strong at turning analysis into insight that drives real business decisions.

This role is for someone who loves getting deep into data, but who also understands that the real value comes from how the story is told. You'll work closely with senior stakeholders, shaping decisions through clear, compelling, and credible insights.

What you'll be doing

Advanced SAS analytics: Use SAS as your core tool to interrogate large, complex datasets and uncover insights that matter.
Insights and storytelling: Translate analysis into clear narratives that influence decisions, not just dashboards and reports.
Business partnership: Work closely with stakeholders across the business to understand their challenges and deliver insights with genuine commercial impact.
Visualisation & reporting: Use tools such as Tableau (or similar) to bring insights to life for non-technical audiences.
Continuous improvement: Proactively identify opportunities to improve processes, methodologies, and the way insights are delivered.
About the team

You'll join a high-performing analytics team that is actively evolving toward a more data science-led environment. It's a space where strong technical foundations are valued, curiosity is encouraged, and you'll have the opportunity to grow your skills as the function matures.

What we're looking for

Proven experience in a Senior Insights Analyst (or similar) role.
Strong, hands-on SAS capability - this is a core requirement, not a nice-to-have.
Solid experience with SQL and data visualisation tools such as Tableau.
The ability to explain complex analysis in a way that resonates with senior, non-technical stakeholders.
A commercial mindset and a genuine passion for using data to influence outcomes.
Exposure to Python and/or R is advantageous but not essential.
Why apply?
This is an opportunity to work in an organisation where analytics genuinely influences strategy and decision-making. You'll have the platform to showcase your SAS expertise, sharpen your storytelling skills, and make a visible impact across the business.

If you're technically strong, commercially minded, and ready to turn data into decisions — we'd love to hear from you.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Business Analyst - Enterprise Transformation

We are seeking experienced Business Analysts to support a large-scale enterprise transformation program, focused on consolidating and redesigning corporate services across a complex organisational environment.

These roles are strongly business-focused, with an emphasis on organisational restructure, operating model design, service definition and process optimisation, supported by enabling technology where appropriate.

The current environment includes significant duplication of business processes and system functionality across similar corporate services, with disparate systems in use. This program aims to address these challenges while also expanding and redefining corporate services where new or enhanced services are identified.

The Role

As a Business Analyst, you will undertake discovery, analysis and design activities to define current and future operating models. You will work closely with a broad range of business and technical stakeholders to identify opportunities for improved service delivery, consolidated processes and better organisational alignment.

Key Responsibilities

Build strong relationships and actively engage with business and technical stakeholders to achieve program outcomes
Facilitate workshops and consultations to elicit, validate and prioritise business requirements
Analyse and document current and future state:
Business processes
User journeys
Business services
Operating and service delivery models
Apply business analysis techniques including business process reviews, functional mapping and capability analysis
Assess the business impacts of organisational, process and system changes and provide high-level advice to support change strategies
Support solution design by translating business needs into clear, structured requirements and functional specifications
Develop options analysis, decision papers and briefing notes to support informed decision-making
Articulate the value of consolidated and improved business processes, including governance, benefits, risks and opportunities

Deliverables

You will be responsible for producing high-quality artefacts including:

Business Requirements Documents (including System Requirements Specifications)
Business process documentation and functional mapping
Service Delivery and Business Operating Model documentation
Options papers, decision papers and briefing notes
Workshop materials and requirements documentation

Skills, Experience & Competencies

To be successful, you will demonstrate:

Proven experience leading facilitation, stakeholder engagement and consensus-building across complex organisational environments
Strong experience in functional analysis, capability analysis and business process mapping
Ability to translate business concepts and requirements into clear, consumable outputs for both business and technical audiences
Experience driving change across large, complex organisations and delivering practical, fit-for-purpose solutions
Ability to manage multiple analysis streams and competing priorities simultaneously
Highly developed communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills with a strong customer-centric mindset

Within Corporate Treasury, the Senior Financial and Banking Analyst is a business-critical position. This role is responsible for managing the organisation's banking function and service level agreements with transactional bankers and related service provider contracts. You will serve as the primary point of contact for critical systems issues that have the potential to impact the organisation's ability to process payroll and accounts payable.

As a senior member of the team, you will act as a trusted advisor, using analytical thinking to propose clear solutions that support informed decision-making at a senior level, including for the Chief Financial Officer and Corporate Treasurer.

Key Responsibilities

Operational Oversight: Monitor and manage banking-related contracts, projects, and relationships to ensure the delivery of the organisation's current and future needs.

Critical Incident Management: Resolve high-impact incidents and problem-solve issues to ensure continued, optimal service delivery.

Project Leadership: Assist in leading banking and financial projects, such as software upgrades and ensuring compliance with Payment Card Industry (PCI) standards.

Strategic Advisory: Support the Corporate Treasurer by evaluating banking-related opportunities and providing recommendations to achieve favourable outcomes.

Technical Development: Maintain an up-to-date understanding of the rapidly changing banking environment and develop specialised banking skills to support projects and business-as-usual activities.

What You Bring to the Team

Analytical Problem Solving: Ability to take ownership of complex banking tasks and initiatives to deliver high-quality outcomes with minimal supervision.

Communication & Engagement: Exceptional skills in building relationships with key stakeholders to jointly evolve options that provide the best value for customers.

Learning & Innovation: A strong desire to develop specialised banking knowledge and understand internal systems, even if you do not have prior banking experience.

Why Apply?

This role offers a unique opportunity to influence long-term financial sustainability through high-profile projects, such as the Customer Centric Payments project and Contemporary Revenue Roadmap. You will be supported by comprehensive procedure notes and a collaborative team environment dedicated to your success. Please note local government experience and senior banking experience is highly desirbale for this role.

Who we are:
At Torrens University Australia, making a difference is in our DNA. As a Certified B Corporation, we belong to a global community of future-focused companies using business as a force for good. A progressive university, we ground our studies in industry. Expert academics bring their insights into the classroom, with a range of assessment types that aim to be authentic and informed by industry needs. Bridging the gap between study and work, our educators prepare students for career success and connect them with future employers. Building relevant skills, experience and networks from day one, students don’t just learn about their industry, they live it.

What’s the job?

As Lead Business Analyst, you will play a pivotal role within a high-visibility, enterprise-wide priority program focused on streamlining and optimising Student Services. This is a hands-on, project-centric leadership role where you will “hold the fort” across multiple interdependent workstreams, ensuring requirements, processes and outcomes are aligned, consistent and delivered to best-practice standards.

 Working closely with senior Project Managers and Program leadership, you will shape and lead Priority initiatives, providing end-to-end business analysis oversight while guiding a small team of Business Analysts. You’ll ensure analysis activities are aligned to standard BA practices, support delivery at pace, and drive meaningful process improvement across the student lifecycle.

 This is a 12-month full-time fixed-term role, suited to a seasoned Lead BA who thrives in complex environments, brings a strong process mindset, and is comfortable operating with influence across dotted-line reporting structures.

Key responsibilities

Lead business analysis activities across a large, multi-stream program, ensuring alignment across priorities, workstreams and delivery teams

Drive end-to-end requirements definition, process mapping and optimisation, with a strong focus on Student Services and operational efficiency

Partner closely with Project Managers and senior stakeholders to shape delivery priorities and sequencing

Ensure BA deliverables align with best-practice Business & Business Analysis (BBA) standards

Champion continuous improvement, embedding process discipline and optimisation approaches across initiatives

Identify risks, dependencies and impacts across workstreams and proactively manage alignment issues

Who you are:

You are a highly experienced Lead Business Analyst with a strong process-driven mindset and a track record of operating within large, complex programs. You are confident leading others, influencing senior stakeholders, and balancing strategic oversight with hands-on delivery.

You bring structure, clarity and momentum to ambiguity and you know how to keep multiple moving parts aligned.

Qualifications and Experience

Minimum 10 years’ experience in Business Analysis, including experience in Lead BA or BA Team Lead roles

Demonstrated experience working on large, complex, multi-workstream programs or portfolios

Proven background in process improvement, optimisation and end-to-end service design

Experience leading small BA teams and operating within dotted-line reporting environments

Experience in the higher education or university sector (highly regarded)

Background in process-driven environments with exposure to Lean, Six Sigma or continuous improvement methodologies

Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to operate effectively in high-visibility initiatives

Technical Skills:

Advanced requirements elicitation, documentation and traceability

Strong process modelling, service mapping and functional design capability

Experience working across Agile and Waterfall delivery models

Solid understanding of SDLC, integrations and enterprise systems

Additional (Nice to have)

Experience with Process Mining tools or techniques to analyse, visualise and optimise end-to-end processes (e.g. identifying bottlenecks, rework and improvement opportunities)

Job Description

The Team

The Technology Solutions Partnering team within SEEK’s Enterprise Technology Services aligns enterprise platforms with business priorities. Working across functional areas and with the teams managing corporate platforms, the team ensures technology investments deliver strategic and commercial outcomes.

The Role

We’re seeking a Senior Technology Solutions Partner who navigates seamlessly between business needs and technology delivery. You’ll partner with leaders across Finance and People & Culture to ensure platforms such as Workday, ServiceNow, Atlassian, and others are aligned to priorities and delivering measurable value. You’ll translate complex requirements into clear decisions, assess vendor and solution fit, and guide investments to strong outcomes.

You bring deep experience across the full technology lifecycle—spanning applications and infrastructure—and a sharp understanding of how enterprise platforms enable corporate functions. You’re financially astute, comfortable analysing costs, modelling ROI, and leading commercial and contractual reviews to maximise value from technology partnerships.

What You’ll Do

Evaluate and shape solution options, balancing cost, risk, and value to meet business outcomes.

Lead vendor assessments and commercial reviews for enterprise platforms, including contracts and pricing.

Provide governance and solution guidance across major programs and initiatives.

Support prioritisation, demand management, and financial analysis across domains and portfolios.

Communicate technical concepts clearly in business-focused language to enable sound decisions.

Build trust and influence across stakeholder groups to achieve alignment and progress.

Qualifications

Extensive experience in technology consulting, business analysis, and enterprise systems.

Proven experience working with Senior Business Leaders in a business partnering role with a deep knowledge of enterprise systems across HR, P&C and finance. 

Proven track record in vendor evaluation, contract assessment, and negotiation.

Strong financial acumen, including spend analysis, ROI modelling, and budget alignment to strategy.

Working knowledge of enterprise platforms and corporate systems (e.g., Workday, Atlassian, ServiceNow).

End-to-end delivery expertise, including project lifecycle management, vendor selection, and solution partnering.

Significant experience with Finance and People & Culture in roles such as Principal Business Analyst, Technology Solutions Partner, or Consultant.

The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year

About the Role

The Technical Business Analyst (BA) drives the successful migration of core business systems (CRM, Client and Candidate onboarding, Applicant Tracking, Job Order Management, Time & Attendance, Pay & Charge, Finance integration) by confirming business requirements/configuring SAS based solutions, designing to-be state business processes, and validating data. The role also leverages solid SQL skills to extract, transform & load data, reconciling data across legacy and target platforms.


Key Responsibilities

Requirements & Process Design
Data Migration Planning and Execution
Project Coordination
Testing & Quality Assurance
Change Management & Training
Go‑Live & Post‑Implementation Support
Compliance & Governance
About You
To succeed in this role, you will be a strong communicator who can build relationships across all levels of the business. You are detail oriented, ready to take on new challenges, and passionate about accuracy and process improvement.

What We Are Looking For:

Education: Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Information Systems, Computer Science, Finance, or related field.
Experience: 3–5 years as a Business Analyst on system implementation or migration projects (ERP, CRM, payroll, finance, etc.).
Proficient in writing SQL selects, joins, sub‑queries, CTEs, and basic data‑cleaning scripts; able to create validation queries and simple stored procedures.
Demonstrated experience in training operational staff on target state systems/processes
Experience with data‑migration utilities (e.g., SSIS) or scripting languages is a plus.
Familiarity with project‑management tools (Jira, Azure DevOps, MS Project) and diagramming tools (Visio, Lucidchart).

Senior Manager - Data Governance

AEMO at the Heart of Energy  

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.    

About the role  

As part of the WA Real-Time Market Monitoring team, you will contribute to the successful operation and ongoing evolution of WA’s Wholesale Electricity Market (WEM) and South West Interconnected System (SWIS). You will receive broad exposure to how the electricity system and market works, in the process gaining a deeper understanding of its intricacies and complexities. You will have the opportunity to develop and excel rapidly in a friendly and diverse team who are driven to succeed. 

This role is based in Perth on a permanent basis. 

What you will be doing  

Responsible for the operation of the WEM Dispatch Engine and Real-Time Market Submissions system, including stakeholder support to Market Participants.

Produce reports and insights on market outcomes for internal and external stakeholders, undertaking complex quantitative and qualitative analysis of market and dispatch data to inform decision making, drive market enhancement and improve transparency.

Identify, manage and resolve real-time and long-term issues that impact efficient and effective operations.

Working closely with the IT support teams, identify, define and test improvements and fixes to several bespoke IT systems.

Provide reliable and quality support to the market 24/7. This is managed on a rotational basis through on-call arrangements with compensation provided.

What you will bring to the role  

Degree in engineering, computing, science, data science or a related discipline.

Experience working within a similar analytical role in a regulated environment. Experience in the WEM/SWIS or other energy market or system will be highly regarded.

Established analysis skills and familiarity working with Python, SQL, and Excel.

Familiarity with Grafana, PI Vision, PowerBI or VBA will also be well regarded.

High attention to detail, coupled with an ability to meet deadlines and prioritise multiple tasks in a dynamic environment. 

In return some of our benefits to you  

Flexible working: work from home, part time, job share, hybrid options, and additional leave options. 

Professional development via projects, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and more. 

Give back with up to 4 days of volunteering leave per year. 

Reward your hard work with annual performance bonuses (subject to eligibility). 

Embrace a healthier you with our wellness program, discounted health insurance, gym perks and our comprehensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP).  

About Our Process

We welcome people of all backgrounds, including people with disabilities and neurodivergence and those who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. Job Title: Data Migration Lead - Insurance Platform - Policy Migration
Ad Text:
Data Migration Lead - Insurance Platform - Policy Migration

Initial 8-month Fixed Term Contract with possible extension

Melbourne CBD, WFH, hybrid

$150k - $200 + Super

The organisation

Talenza is partnering with a leading professional services organisation undertaking a major core platform transformation. This program is focused on modernising policy administration capabilities and delivering a scalable, future-ready insurance core environment.

This is a critical role within the transformation, responsible for ensuring the accurate, secure, and performant migration of complex legacy policy data into a modern core insurance platform.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the end-to-end data migration workstream within a core insurance platform transformation; Duck Creek, GuideWire, Sapiens or equivalent.
Own migration planning, scope definition, sequencing, and delivery across multiple sprints
Design, configure, test, and execute data migration runs into the target core platform
Analyse complex legacy data structures and work with business and data analysts to define data mappings and transformation rules
Define and manage user stories, acceptance criteria, estimates, and sprint outcomes for the migration stream
Oversee the full data loading lifecycle, including pre-load validation, execution, reconciliation, and post-load verification
Optimise migration performance to support large data volumes, cutover windows, and agreed SLAs
Identify, investigate, and resolve data quality issues, defects, and performance bottlenecks
Collaborate closely with BAs, data analysts, legacy SMEs, ETL developers, integration teams, and QA
Provide hands-on technical contribution where required to ensure delivery outcomes are met
Lead and coordinate ETL developers and support resources within the migration team

Key Skills & Experience

5+ years' hands-on experience delivering data migration for core insurance platforms
Proven experience migrating data from mainframe or complex legacy policy systems
Strong understanding of the insurance policy lifecycle, including policy, endorsements, customers, and reference data
End-to-end knowledge of the data migration lifecycle, from source analysis through to production load
Solid experience with ETL concepts, data processing, and transformation logic
Strong SQL skills for data validation, reconciliation, and defect analysis
Experience working with relational and/or NoSQL databases
Demonstrated ability to lead and mentor ETL or data migration delivery teams
Comfortable operating in Agile delivery environments and working across small, fast-moving teams

Benefits

Lead one of the most critical streams in a major insurance transformation
High-impact role with genuine ownership and visibility
Competitive $150k-$200k + super package on an 8-month FTC with possible extension
Opportunity to work on a modern core insurance platform with long-term relevance

Job Title: Head of Investor Relations & External Communications
Ad Text:
An established, growth-focused Australian organisation with a global footprint is seeking an experienced Head of Investor Relations & External Communications to lead its engagement with investors, analysts, media and external stakeholders.

This is a senior, highly visible role that will act as the voice behind the organisation’s corporate story, ensuring clear, consistent and credible messaging across all external channels. Partnering closely with the CEO, CFO, Board and executive leadership team, you will play a pivotal role in shaping how the company is understood by the investment community and the broader market.

The Role:

Reporting directly to the Group CFO, this role is responsible for developing and executing comprehensive investor relations and external communications strategies that support long-term growth, protect reputation and strengthen investor confidence.

You will serve as the primary point of contact for investors and analysts, oversee market-facing communications, and provide insights drawn from investor sentiment, market intelligence and peer performance to inform strategic decision-making.

Key Responsibilities:

Build, maintain and strengthen relationships with existing and prospective investors

Act as the primary contact for investor and analyst enquiries

Plan and deliver investor events, roadshows, site visits, strategy days and conferences

Lead the preparation of investor presentations, market announcements and results communications

Manage and analyse investor feedback, sentiment and market consensus

Partner with senior leadership to align investor messaging with business strategy

Investor Targeting & Market Intelligence:

Develop strategies to broaden and diversify the investor base

Monitor analyst coverage, recommendations and market consensus

Track share price performance relative to peers and the broader market

Analyse market trends, macroeconomic factors and competitor performance

Provide actionable insights to support executive and Board decision-making

External Communications & Media:

Develop and execute a cohesive external communications and media strategy aligned to investor messaging

Build and maintain strong relationships with key media and journalists

Manage reputational risk and respond to media and market issues as required

Oversee the delivery of key external publications such as annual and sustainability reports

Support internal communications to ensure employees are informed, engaged and aligned with company performance and direction

Financial Reporting & Governance:

Partner closely with finance to ensure accuracy, transparency and consistency in financial disclosures

Support regulatory and governance-related communications, including AGMs

Safety & Sustainability:

Demonstrate leadership in safety, health, environmental and sustainability practices, ensuring communications reflect organisational values and responsibilities

About you:

You are a seasoned investor relations and communications leader with strong credibility in capital/ ASX-listed market environments. You bring gravitas, strategic insight and the ability to distil complex financial information into clear, compelling narratives.

Key experience & capabilities:

Tertiary qualifications in Investor Relations, Communications, Finance or a related discipline

Minimum 10 years’ experience in investor relations and/or corporate and financial communications (ASX-listed experience highly regarded)

Strong background in equity capital markets and working with analysts and institutional investors

Demonstrated experience in ASX announcements, results communications, annual reports and AGMs

Exceptional written, presentation and public speaking skills

Proven ability to manage media, reputational risk and complex stakeholder issues

High level of financial and strategic acumen

Strong understanding of ESG and sustainability reporting

Confident, composed and effective in high-pressure environments

Experience leveraging digital and social platforms for investor and external communications

Why join?

This is a rare opportunity to step into a senior, influential role where you will shape how a complex, growing organisation is perceived by the market. With flexible part-time options (0.6 or 0.8 FTE), the role offers meaningful impact, executive-level exposure and the chance to build a long-term, global investor narrative.

To submit an application please APPLY via APPLY NOW
